race.description: Onecall Steel And Form Showcase Handicap (Bm58)
race.comment: WONDERFUL MISTAKE (12) went back from the wide draw and produced a solid set of figures late when fifth over 1000m at Canberra. Progressive filly who should prove too good for these from the good gate. ROYAL MEMORY (10) showed good early dash on resumption when a fighting second over 1010m at this track. Clearly come back well and no surprise to see her go one better. SILVER SERENADE (11) talented filly kept fresh for this after scoring a big win over 1100m at Gundagai on November 14. Concussion plates go on and not sure where she gets to from the draw. Each way. OUR LITTLE STAR (3) win record hardly excites but getting fitter with racing. Gripped on late with the big weight when sixth over 1000m at Canberra. Stays in the mix.
